**********************************************************************
*             HMS DRIFT CHAMBERS CALIBRATION PROCEDURES              *
*								     *
*                         Author: Carlos Yero                        *
*                       Date: December 23, 2016                      *
*                                                                    *
**********************************************************************

The Drift Chambers calibration procedures SUMMARY:
0) Add average drift time distributions per plane to root file 

1) Get individual sense wire drift time distribution per plane

2) Extract the "t0" value on a wire-by-wire basis, calculate
   the "t0" weighted average and assign it to the plane in question

3) Add the weighted "t0" values to the 'h_drifttime_offsets'  in the
   hdc.param file 

4) Add the "t0" correction to the drift time spectra obtained in step (0)

5) Create a lookup table (hdriftmap.param) of values for each plane 
   based on integratig the "t0" corrected drift time spectra for each 
   plane.

6) Run the hallc_replay script on the raw data file, having updated
   the hdc.param and hdriftmap.param files. 

NOTE: The root file produced should have the updated drift distance 
      spectra corresponding to the changes made in the parameter files.
      

***************************IMPORTANT****************************
A detailed explanation of each step is given in the directories
pertaining to the drift chamber calibration. (SEE README files) 
-- Look in the 'hms_dc_t_Zero' directory  to START
****************************************************************





